title: Los Jalapenos
typeOfFood: Lacto, Ovo, Beer/Wine, Take-out, Mexican, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Mexican restaurant whose menu has a few dishes that can be made vegan. The Santa Fe guacamole, made table-side, is a filling appetizer consisting of guacamole with black beans and corn. You could get the veggie fajita and omit sour cream and the pre-made guacamole (contains sour cream). Staff says beans are not cooked in animal fat.
